## Verification checklist

- Repository state and existing changes were inspected before editing.
- Milestone prerequisites and allowed files were identified.
- The implementation is the smallest complete slice.
- No unrelated or future-milestone work was introduced.
- Existing user changes were preserved.
- Tests were not weakened and hidden fallbacks were not added.
- Verification depth matches the change risk.
- Every unrun test is explicitly reported as `not run` with a reason.
- Every changed line is justified by the user request, owner PRD, failing test, or required integration.
- Any expansion beyond initially allowed files was justified and reported.
- No abstractions, fallbacks, future-proofing, or unrelated cleanup were introduced.